1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,800
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:07,240
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:07,240 --> 00:00:11,520
And my name is Katherine and today we've got a great lesson for you about traveling
我是Katherine，今天我们有一节关于旅行的精彩课程，

4
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:13,000
and getting directions.
以及如何问路。

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,000
That's right.
没错。

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:18,680
So sometimes we are looking for an address, we are looking for our friend's house and
所以有时候我们在找地址，找朋友家，

7
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:19,840
we can't find it.
却找不到。

8
00:00:19,840 --> 00:00:20,840
So what do you have to do?
那你该怎么办呢？

9
00:00:20,840 --> 00:00:23,680
You have to stop and ask someone for directions.
你得停下来找人问路。

10
00:00:23,680 --> 00:00:29,240
There's actually a joke in many countries that men hate to ask for directions.
在很多国家其实有个笑话，说男人讨厌问路。

11
00:00:29,240 --> 00:00:34,400
And so this is the women's approach, asking and getting directions and finally finding
所以这就是女人的做法：问路、得到指引，最终找到

12
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:35,400
your way.
你的路。

13
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:36,400
So it's a good thing.
所以这是件好事。

14
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,880
That's a very good thing.
这是件非常好的事。

15
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:40,280
So we're going to jump right into the dialogue.
那我们直接进入对话吧。

16
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:49,920
Let's see what happens here and if they can find the place they're looking for.
看看这里发生了什么，他们能不能找到要找的地方。

17
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:52,040
We've been going around in circles for the past hour.
我们过去一个小时一直在兜圈子。

18
00:00:52,040 --> 00:00:55,180
Will you just please stop and ask for directions?
你能不能停下来问个路？

19
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,600
We are not lost.
我们没迷路。

20
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,320
I'm just taking the scenic route.
我只是在走风景路线。

21
00:00:58,320 --> 00:00:59,440
Yeah, whatever.
是啊，随便你怎么说。

22
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:02,320
I told you we should buy that GPS that was on sale.
我告诉过你我们应该买那个打折的GPS。

23
00:01:02,320 --> 00:01:03,480
But would you listen to me?
可你听我的吗？

24
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:05,640
No, this is so typical.
不，这太典型了。

25
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:06,640
Fine.
好吧。

26
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:10,480
I'll ask this guy for directions if it will shut your trap.
如果这能让你闭嘴，我就去问那个人路。

27
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:11,480
Excuse me, sir.
打扰一下，先生。

28
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,760
Can you tell me how to get to St. Mary's Church?
你能告诉我怎么去圣玛丽教堂吗？

29
00:01:14,760 --> 00:01:15,760
Sure.
当然。

30
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:23,680
Go down Park Road, turn left, go up as far as the set of traffic lights and turn left.
沿着公园路走，左转，一直走到红绿灯处再左转。

31
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:27,600
The place you're looking for is the second building on the right.
你要找的地方是右边第二栋楼。

32
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:28,600
Thanks.
谢谢。

33
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:30,520
See, was that hard?
看，有那么难吗？

34
00:01:30,520 --> 00:01:34,160
If you would only listen to me more often, you'd be better off.
如果你多听我的，你会过得更好。

35
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:38,560
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

36
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:43,600
So well, the woman was obviously a little bit angry that the guy refused to admit that
嗯，那个女人显然有点生气，因为那个男人拒绝承认

37
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:44,600
he was lost.
他迷路了。

38
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,600
That's right.
没错。

39
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,600
She's very frustrated.
她非常沮丧。

40
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:50,720
And this has been in movies and in books and all sorts of things.
这在电影、书籍和各种东西里都有体现。

41
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:54,240
This kind of story of the man not wanting to ask for directions.
这种男人不想问路的故事。

42
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:58,480
And so he keeps saying, listen, I've got these excuses.
所以他一直说，听着，我有这些借口。

43
00:01:58,480 --> 00:02:00,920
I'm taking the scenic route, for example.
比如，我在走风景路线。

44
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:01,920
That's right.
没错。

45
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:07,280
And that's our first word for today on Language Takeaway.
这就是我们今天“语言小贴士”的第一个词。

46
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:09,040
Language Takeaway.
语言小贴士。

47
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:11,960
So as you say, the scenic route, what does he mean by that?
所以正如你所说，风景路线，他是什么意思？

48
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:17,360
Okay, route is like a path or a trail or kind of like the way that you go somewhere.
好的，route就像一条路径或小道，或者说是你去某地的路线。

49
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,920
So the route to my house.
比如去我家的路线。

50
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:24,280
But in this case, the scenic route or the scenic route, you can say in both ways, is
但在这里，scenic route或the scenic route，两种说法都可以，指的是

51
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,800
the most beautiful way to go.
最美丽的路线。

52
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:28,280
It's usually the longer one.
通常也是更长的路线。

53
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,280
Yeah.
是的。

54
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,200
So you can say, oh, it's just the scenic route.
所以你可以说，哦，只是风景路线。

55
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,200
It's not really true.
这不一定是真的。

56
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:33,760
It's just the longer route.
只是更长的路线。

57
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:34,960
Right, exactly.
对，没错。

58
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:36,720
So that's the excuse that he's giving her.
所以这就是他给她的借口。

59
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:37,960
He's like, no, I'm not lost.
他说，不，我没迷路。

60
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:41,400
We're taking longer because, well, we're taking the beautiful route.
我们走得更长是因为，嗯，我们在走美丽的路线。

61
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:44,080
All right, with all the trees and the animals and the lakes.
有树、动物和湖泊。

62
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,080
No, I don't.
不，我不信。

63
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,080
I don't buy it.
我不买账。

64
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,080
I don't believe this.
我不相信这个。

65
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,080
That's right.
没错。

66
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:49,080
I don't believe it.
我不信。

67
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,080
I don't believe it.
我不信。

68
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,080
Whatever.
随便吧。

69
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,080
You know what?
你知道吗？

70
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,080
We need a GPS.
我们需要一个GPS。

71
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:55,080
Okay, GPS, global positioning system.
好的，GPS，全球定位系统。

72
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:58,280
So many people have these in their cars these days.
现在很多人车里都有这个。

73
00:02:58,280 --> 00:03:05,680
This is like an electronic map that will use your location to show you where to go.
这就像一个电子地图，会根据你的位置告诉你往哪走。

74
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,000
It's very useful.
非常有用。

75
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:12,560
And especially in places like the United States that have streets that are clearly marked
尤其是在像美国这样的地方，街道标记清晰，

76
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:15,800
and it's just a little bit easier to get around.
出行稍微容易一些。

77
00:03:15,800 --> 00:03:19,840
You can just get in your car, type in the address you want to go to and the thing talks
你只需上车，输入你想去的地址，然后这个东西会

78
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,840
to you.
跟你说话。

79
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:23,160
It says turn left, go straight, turn right.
它会说左转、直行、右转。

80
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,160
Creepy.
有点诡异。

81
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:26,600
So this is a very useful device.
所以这是一个非常有用的设备。

82
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:30,240
It's like a computer that you use in your computer, a GPS.
它就像一台你用在电脑里的电脑，一个GPS。

83
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:37,320
All right, so she's talking about the GPS and then at the end of that line, she says,
好了，她正在谈论GPS，然后在那句话的结尾，她说，

84
00:03:37,320 --> 00:03:39,440
this is so typical.
这太典型了。

85
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:40,440
So what?
那又怎样？

86
00:03:40,440 --> 00:03:41,440
Getting lost.
迷路。

87
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:43,720
All right, getting lost is so typical.
好了，迷路太典型了。

88
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:47,680
So something that is typical is common.
所以典型的东西就是常见的。

89
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:48,960
This is so normal.
这太正常了。

90
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:50,080
This is so typical.
这太典型了。

91
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:53,080
This is so something you normally do.
这是你通常做的事情。

92
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:55,860
So what other examples could we give with the word typical?
那么，我们还能用“典型”这个词举出什么其他例子呢？

93
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:56,860
Something that is typical?
什么是典型的东西？

94
00:03:56,860 --> 00:03:59,520
Okay, well, you can have a behavior like this.
好吧，你可以有这样的行为。

95
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,640
What he did was typical.
他做的事很典型。

96
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:08,280
We can also say, in my typical Saturday, I wake up late and drink a coffee and take a
我们也可以说，在我典型的星期六，我晚起，喝杯咖啡，然后小睡

97
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,280
nap.
一会儿。

98
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:10,280
Okay, cool.
好的，不错。

99
00:04:10,280 --> 00:04:13,160
So it's common, it's regular, it's frequent maybe.
所以它是常见的、常规的，也许频繁的。

100
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,160
That's right.
没错。

101
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,880
Or you go out to dinner and your friend is late.
或者你出去吃饭，你的朋友迟到了。

102
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:18,760
You say, oh, this is so typical of him.
你说，哦，这太典型了，他就是这样。

103
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:20,680
Right, he's always late.
对，他总是迟到。

104
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:21,680
Very good.
非常好。

105
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:26,000
All right, and we have one last set of words here.
好了，我们还有最后一组词。

106
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:30,920
And when the guy was giving him instructions, he said, you know what, go left, go right,
当那个人给他指路时，他说，你知道吗，向左走，向右走，

107
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:31,920
whatever.
随便。

108
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:35,240
And then he said, until you reach the set of traffic lights.
然后他说，直到你到达那组红绿灯。

109
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,520
So what is a traffic light?
那么什么是红绿灯？

110
00:04:36,520 --> 00:04:38,360
Well, you know what a light is.
嗯，你知道什么是灯。

111
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:39,400
You know what traffic is.
你知道什么是交通。

112
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:43,080
Traffic is cars driving on the road, trucks, things like that.
交通就是路上行驶的汽车、卡车之类的东西。

113
00:04:43,080 --> 00:04:47,840
So traffic light is a special light with three colors, red, yellow, and green.
所以红绿灯是一种特殊的灯，有三种颜色：红、黄、绿。

114
00:04:47,840 --> 00:04:49,960
And it tells you if you can stop or go.
它告诉你是否可以停车或通行。

115
00:04:49,960 --> 00:04:52,440
So they're also called stop lights, right?
所以它们也叫停车灯，对吧？

116
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,440
That's right.
没错。

117
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:54,440
Okay.
好的。

118
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:56,980
So stop lights and traffic lights is the same thing.
所以停车灯和红绿灯是同一个东西。

119
00:04:56,980 --> 00:05:00,480
Usually they hang from above the street.
通常它们悬挂在街道上方。

120
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,620
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

121
00:05:02,620 --> 00:05:03,620
Words and phrases there.
那里有单词和短语。

122
00:05:03,620 --> 00:05:11,720
Why don't we listen to our dialogue again and we'll be back in just a little bit.
我们为什么不重新听一遍我们的对话，我们一会儿就回来。

123
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,200
We've been going around in circles for the past hour.
我们过去一个小时一直在兜圈子。

124
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:17,040
Will you just please stop and ask for directions?
你能不能停下来问个路？

125
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,440
We are not lost.
我们没有迷路。

126
00:05:18,440 --> 00:05:20,160
I'm just taking the scenic route.
我只是在走风景路线。

127
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,280
Yeah, whatever.
是啊，随便吧。

128
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:24,160
I told you we should buy that GPS that was on sale.
我告诉过你我们应该买那个打折的GPS。

129
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,360
But would you listen to me?
但你听我的吗？

130
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,440
No, this is so typical.
不，这太典型了。

131
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:28,440
Fine.
好吧。

132
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:32,280
I'll ask this guy for directions if it will shut your trap.
如果这能让你闭嘴，我就去问那个人路。

133
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,280
Excuse me, sir.
打扰一下，先生。

134
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:36,640
Can you tell me how to get to St. Mary's Church?
你能告诉我怎么去圣玛丽教堂吗？

135
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:37,640
Sure.
当然。

136
00:05:37,640 --> 00:05:45,520
Go down Park Road, turn left, go up as far as the set of traffic lights and turn left.
沿着公园路走，左转，一直走到红绿灯处，然后左转。

137
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:49,520
The place you're looking for is the second building on the right.
你要找的地方是右边第二栋楼。

138
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:50,520
Thanks.
谢谢。

139
00:05:50,520 --> 00:05:52,380
See, was that hard?
看，这难吗？

140
00:05:52,380 --> 00:05:55,760
If you would only listen to me more often, you'd be better off.
如果你能多听我的话，你会过得更好。

141
00:05:55,760 --> 00:06:04,200
All right, we've got some great phrases coming up in Fluency Builder.
好了，我们在流利度构建器中有一些很棒的短语。

142
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,200
Fluency Builder.
流利度构建器。

143
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:08,960
So the first phrase that we're going to look at is what the wife said at the very beginning.
所以我们要看的第一个短语是妻子一开始说的。

144
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:14,520
She said, we have been going around in circles for the past hour.
她说，我们过去一个小时一直在兜圈子。

145
00:06:14,520 --> 00:06:16,440
Going around in circles.
兜圈子。

146
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:19,160
So we could say we've been driving in circles.
所以我们可以说我们一直在开车兜圈子。

147
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:24,640
In circles means you've been making the same route over and over and over again.
兜圈子意味着你一遍又一遍地走同一条路线。

148
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:28,560
You keep seeing the same house, the same tree, the same house, the same tree.
你一直看到同一栋房子、同一棵树、同一栋房子、同一棵树。

149
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:31,080
So this means we're not going anywhere.
所以这意味着我们哪儿也没去。

150
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:35,480
You could also say, Marco, I wish you had brought the map.
你也可以说，马可，我希望你带了地图。

151
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:38,240
We've been walking in circles for two hours.
我们已经走了两个小时圈子了。

152
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,360
Okay, cool.
好的，不错。

153
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:43,920
So you can use it if you're driving or if you're walking in any situation like that.
所以如果你在开车或走路，任何类似的情况下都可以用。

154
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:44,920
Exactly.
完全正确。

155
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,920
Okay, good.
好的，很好。

156
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:47,560
All right, so going around in circles.
好了，所以是兜圈子。

157
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:53,440
Now, moving on, the guy was a little bit irritated with her and he said something that's a little
现在，继续，那个男人对她有点恼火，他说了一些有点

158
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,440
bit impolite.
不礼貌的话。

159
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,440
He said, you know what?
他说，你知道吗？

160
00:06:55,440 --> 00:06:58,960
I'm going to ask for directions if it will shut your trap.
如果这能让你闭嘴，我就去问路。

161
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,440
Impolite, this is rude.
不礼貌，这很粗鲁。

162
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:02,320
Yeah, this is very rude.
是的，这非常粗鲁。

163
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,680
So be careful when you use this.
所以使用时要小心。

164
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:07,000
You can say, hey, shut your trap.
你可以说，嘿，闭上你的嘴。

165
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,880
Okay, so shut means to close.
好，shut 意思是关闭。

166
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:12,440
But trap, this is your mouth.
但 trap，这是你的嘴巴。

167
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,440
Okay.
好。

168
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,440
So your mouth is a trap.
所以你的嘴巴是个陷阱。

169
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:15,440
It's kind of like a trap.
有点像陷阱。

170
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:20,400
In this case, shut your trap is a set phrase and it means shut up.
在这种情况下，shut your trap 是一个固定短语，意思是闭嘴。

171
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,400
Be quiet.
安静点。

172
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,520
Stop talking.
别说话了。

